{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683023,"nonce":"jcV+0yy+ztRlNkwuHKgfP+tRml0=","title":"Scalar expressions: CASE, COALESCE, NULLIF, and string/date functions","message":"Expression support is limited to comparisons, null checks, logical ops, and the four arithmetic operators. Missing scalar building blocks:\n\n- CASE WHEN ... THEN ... ELSE ... END (searched and simple forms).\n- COALESCE(a, b, ...) and NULLIF(a, b) — note COALESCE collapses nullability, so the result type can become non-null when a fallback is non-null.\n- Common string functions: lower, upper, length, trim, concat / || , substring.\n- Common date/time functions (extract, date_trunc, now) — useful alongside the existing timestamp column types.\n\nThese are expression constructors in `crates/squealy/src/expr.rs` with rendering in each backend sql.rs. COALESCE/NULLIF in particular interact with the new Option\u003cT\u003e nullability model, so the value-type/nullability mapping needs to be part of the design.","files":null}]}